import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    species_count = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    species_count.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Wildlife Species')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wildlife species involved in bird strikes?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'], data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'])
    plt.xlabel('Speed (knots)')
    plt.ylabel('Amount of Damage')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between aircraft speed and amount of damage caused by bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    phase_counts = data['Phase_of_flight'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(phase_counts, labels=phase_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of bird strikes by phase of flight?", wrap=True)
    return plt;
